</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFFB9850AFF13FABCFCFFF9E1" blockId="30.[136,1452,1310,1661]" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB9850AFF13FABCFEE9FAC0" bold="true" box="[189,294,1346,1372]" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB9850AFE88FABCFE35FAC0" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[294,506,1346,1372]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB9850AFE88FABCFE35FAC0" box="[294,506,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Myoxanthus merae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small, caespitose species with slender ramicauls and narrow leaves and producing successive single flowers. It can be recognized by the yellowish flowers with the red to yellowish sepals that are pubescent externally, basally ovate petals then narrower with revolute margins, a red-brownish elliptical, oblong lip, weakly trilobed, with lateral lobes erect below the middle, disc with a pair of longitudinal calli near the centre and a pair of small auricles at its truncate base. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB9850AFDFDFA2CFCA6FA70" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" box="[595,873,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplicaulis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB9850AFDFDFA2CFCA6FA70" box="[595,873,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Myoxanthus simplicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB9850AFC02FA2CFBD0FA70" box="[940,1055,1490,1516]" name="Venezuela" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB9850AFBFAFA2CFB64FA70" box="[1108,1195,1490,1516]" name="Guyana" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Guyana</collectingCountry>
has a similar habit and flowers. However, the latter has wider petals with a more pronounced, narrow, thick apical section, more pronounced, oblique lateral lobes of the lip and a pair of longitudinal calli emerging below the middle that extend to the base. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB9850AFF26F9C0FE90F9C4" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[136,351,1598,1624]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB9850AFF26F9C0FE90F9C4" box="[136,351,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Myoxanthus merae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been previously recorded only from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB9850AFC9CF9C0FC5EF9C4" box="[818,913,1598,1624]" name="Ecuador" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, but the photograph reproduced here (Fig. 15E) is from a plant collected in Tingo María National Park, 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB9850AFD5BF99DFCE3F9E1" box="[757,812,1635,1661]" name="Peru" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
